Hi #{@user.handle},
\
It's been a while since I sent an Exercism newsletter! That's because we've been super-busy building our brand new platform for learning to code in the LLM era - Jiki (https://jiki.io). And I'm very excited to tell you that we're now live and you can sign up today: https://jiki.io
\
If you'd like to know more, I'm hosting an Ask Me Anything to discuss Jiki, Exercism, and the future of coding in general on Saturday 11th July at 12:00 UTC. You can set a reminder on YouTube now: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZYDSF2jtKkg
\
INTRODUCING JIKI
\
Jiki (https://jiki.io) is a brand new platform by the team behind Exercism. It's designed for beginners, juniors and vibe-coders wanting to understand what's going on under the hood. It has two halves:
\
* Coding Fundamentals: The most fun and effective way to get a solid understanding of coding basics, with hundreds of hours of exercises to solve, projects to build, and videos to learn from.
* Build with Jeremy: A series of livestreams where I build real products and teach you everything I know along the way, then set you projects where you put that knowledge into action. Even if you're experienced at coding, this might be a fun way to explore new areas!
\
Jiki is 100% free to sign up to with Premium options if you want some bonus features. The Coding Fundamentals part is currently available for JavaScript (with Python coming later in the year), and the Build with Jeremy half starts on July 11th (set a reminder here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aEmZE-VnxsQ).
\
TRANSLATING EXERCISM AND JIKI
\
I'm also excited to announce that we're going to be rolling out translations of both Exercism (https://exercism.org) and Jiki (https://jiki.io) to dozens of languages over the next two months. We'll be hosting a translatathon (like a hackathon but less code and more translating) later in the month.
\
